<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E08FF8648A75202FE0CF8EA" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418E08FF8648A75202FC56F906" blockId="70.[151,1436,1326,1999]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E08FF8648A75202FE31FAB7" bold="true" box="[151,404,1326,1351]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Description of Male.</emphasis>
Fully winged; length 2.0– 
<quantity id="C731ABA48E08FF864AEC5202FC9CFAB6" box="[732,825,1326,1350]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.9 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible, clypeus and anterior margin of face testaceous; antenna brown, except proximal half of segment 1 testaceous; mesosoma black; metasoma brown; legs testaceous, except stalk of metafemur, posterior extremity of metatibia and part of metatarsus darkened; occasionally legs testaceous, except proximal extremity of metacoxa brown. Antenna filiform; antennal segments in following proportions: 10:5:8:10:9.5:10:9:9:8:10.5. Head shiny, punctate, unsculptured among punctures; frontal line incomplete, very slight, only present in front of anterior ocellus; POL = 7; OL = 4; OOL = 11; OPL = 5; TL = 7; greatest breadth of posterior ocelli as long as OL; occipital carina complete. Scutum and scutellum shiny, punctate, unsculptured among punctures. Notauli incomplete, reaching approximately 0.3–04 length of scutum. Metanotum dull, slightly rugose. Propodeum without strong transverse keel between dorsal and posterior surface; dorsal surface reticulate rugose; posterior surface with two complete longitudinal keels and median area as rugose as lateral areas. Fore wing hyaline, without dark transverse bands; stigmal vein forming angle between distal and proximal part; distal part of stigmal vein shorter than proximal part (6.5:8). Paramere (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E08FF86495A51F2FE70F906" box="[362,469,1758,1782]" captionStart="PLATE 17" captionStartId="68.[151,233,1880,1903]" captionTargetBox="[180,1401,211,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-120@68.[166,1421,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="68" captionText="PLATE 17. A, D–F. Male genitalia. B. Pronotum and scutum. C, G. Chelae, holotypes. A. Anteon abatanense, holotype (from Olmi 1991). B. A. achterbergi, female from UAE, dorsal view. C. A. achterbergi (from Olmi 1991). D. A. achterbergi from UAE (from Olmi 2008a). E. A. adebratti, holotype (from Olmi 1993d). F. A. amabile, holotype (from Xu et al. 2006a). G. A. acre (from Olmi 1991). Scale bar 0.11 mm for A, 0.17 mm for C and G, 0.14 mm for D and E, 0.19 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278432" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278432/files/figure.png" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Plate 17F</figureCitation>
) without distal inner process. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418E08FF8648F7502FFE0CF8EA" blockId="70.[151,1436,1326,1999]" box="[199,425,1794,1819]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E08FF8648F7502FFE80F8EB" bold="true" box="[199,293,1795,1819]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
